  "texts": [
    "This customization technique, known as transfer learning, allows a general model to be easily applied to other fields.",
    "The term \"large\" in large language models refers to the significant expansion in parameter scale compared to early small models.",
    "Early small models were trained with a limited number of parameters and smaller datasets, making supervision and review relatively easy.",
    "Although large language models use network architectures and training methods similar to those of smaller pre-trained language models, they achieve impressive performance improvements by expanding the scale of parameters, datasets, and computational resources.",
    "These models have demonstrated for the first time the ability of a single model to effectively solve many complex tasks."
  ],
